112
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:15,430
Even on the CCTV footages,

113
00:08:15,430 --> 00:08:17,140
he was mostly alone wherever it was,

114
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:19,540
such as break rooms and the cafeteria.

115
00:08:21,890 --> 00:08:27,150
By the way, there are so many clubs and organizations within Silver Lining, aren't there?

116
00:08:27,150 --> 00:08:28,370
It's my management philosophy.

117
00:08:28,370 --> 00:08:30,510
One club per employee,

118
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,260
being mindful of the employees' welfare.

119
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:34,770
Isn't it a little weird?

120
00:08:34,770 --> 00:08:36,060
What's weird?

121
00:08:36,060 --> 00:08:38,780
An outsider by choice joins the hiking club.

122
00:08:38,780 --> 00:08:40,890
It's just formality.

123
00:08:40,890 --> 00:08:42,100
There's no meaning to it.

124
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:44,030
Oh, is that so?

125
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:45,880
Then did you also...

126
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:48,820
- join a club, Se Yeon?
- Sorry?

127
00:08:49,810 --> 00:08:51,180
Yes.

128
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:53,290
What club did you join?

129
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:55,550
Entrepreneurial? English?

130
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:59,170
Or maybe... movies?

131
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,600
The Comedy Club.

132
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:09,660
The Comedy Club provides the most support funds.

133
00:09:09,660 --> 00:09:13,150
Then do you have a personal talent?

134
