We also have things we heard from Mr. Nam.

263
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:40,990
I'm not sure what you heard from whom, but...

264
00:18:40,990 --> 00:18:44,350
cornering me without any evidence like this...

265
00:18:44,350 --> 00:18:46,760
I honestly find it unpleasant.

266
00:18:55,170 --> 00:18:57,770
Okay, enjoy your food.

267
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,450
My daughter!

268
00:19:14,450 --> 00:19:16,670
Are you on a date with Mom?

269
00:19:16,670 --> 00:19:18,260
Yes, we're buying some clothes.

270
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:19,680
It's Dad.

271
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:22,580
I told you to eat properly even if it's cumbersome.

272
00:19:22,580 --> 00:19:25,710
No, I had a quick meal just today.

273
00:19:25,710 --> 00:19:27,790
What's going on, though? At this hour?

274
00:19:27,790 --> 00:19:29,250
Nothing's going on.

275
00:19:29,250 --> 00:19:31,590
I called because I wanted to see my family.

276
00:19:31,590 --> 00:19:34,780
Dad, can I buy tickets to the BTS concert?

277
00:19:34,780 --> 00:19:37,980
They came to New York this time, but the tickets were a bit expensive.

278
00:19:37,980 --> 00:19:39,440
Sure, buy them.

279
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,620
Don't worry about it.

280
00:19:40,620 --> 00:19:43,170
I'm an executive at Beomyeong.

281
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:48,390
You do everything you want there and see everything you want to see–

282
00:19:48,390 --> 00:19:50,690
Dad, I'm sorry. I'm getting a call from a friend.

283
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:53,110
- I'll call you later.
- M-Min Ju.

284
00:19:53,110 --> 00:19:55,490
Gosh, that girl...

285
00:19:56,440 --> 00:20:00,550
Aigoo, daddy is her lowest priority.

286
00:20:00,550 --> 00:20:02,400
Aigoo.

287
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:08,210
When will you be coming to Korea?

288
00:20:20,670 --> 00:20:24,760
Director Kwak claimed he didn't know anything with a straight face.

289
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:26,590
I need an ISE.

290
00:20:26,590 --> 00:20:28,550
Are you guys detectives?

291
00:20:28,550 --> 00:20:30,190
Evidence, my ass.

292
00:20:30,190 --> 00:20:32,230
You only need to hang him.

293
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:33,670
Do you want to hear another confession?

294
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:36,060
I'm sure that's how you've always been.

295
00:20:36,060 --> 00:20:38,350
You're not even a human.

296
00:20:40,130 --> 00:20:40,930
What?

297
00:20:40,930 --> 00:20:45,580
I'm saying we'll be locked up if we act on him rashly.

298
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:49,090
W-Wow, a car!

299
00:20:53,910 --> 00:20:56,310
Gosh, where is my head?

300
00:20:56,310 --> 00:20:59,830
I-I forgot something...

301
00:20:59,830 --> 00:21:03,260
We became one team. We should at least have our first staff dinner.

302
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,400
Here you go.

303
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:12,550
The entrees will come out soon.

304
00:21:12,550 --> 00:21:15,320
Okay, thank you.

305
00:21:15,320 --> 00:21:16,810
Cheers.

306
00:21:27,730 --> 00:21:31,010
Shouldn't it be a given that a bodyguard doesn't drink?

307
00:21:31,010 --> 00:21:33,600
Do I need to tell you even these things?

308
00:21:46,250 --> 00:21:48,490
W-Well,

309
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:50,500
since work hours are over...

310
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:55,440
Work hours are over? Then I'll be taking my leave first.

311
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:58,390
Gosh, it's nice!

312
00:22:01,020 --> 00:22:02,730
Se Yeon!

313
00:22:05,740 --> 00:22:08,160
It must be so nice to be a good person, In Seong.

314
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,960
Forgiving and making up so easily.

315
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:13,330
I'm sorry, but I can't do that.

316
00:22:21,820 --> 00:22:23,380
Wait–

317
00:22:31,150 --> 00:22:32,750
President Kim, I can't do this.

318
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:34,780
If you're the one who brought in a person like him,

319
00:22:34,780 --> 00:22:37,330
then you should've been prepared

320
00:22:37,330 --> 00:22:39,320
for this much, at least.

321
00:22:39,320 --> 00:22:43,360
Relationships with other people are always the hardest thing.

322
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:45,120
That's right.

323
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:48,460
However, I'm not the one best suited for working out relationships,

324
00:22:48,460 --> 00:22:50,510
you are, In Seong.

325
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,870
I mean, that's true.

326
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:13,390
Excuse me... could I get it to go?

327
00:23:14,730 --> 00:23:16,540
They'll get way too soggy.

328
00:23:16,540 --> 00:23:18,570
Yes, they'll get soggy. Okay.

329
00:23:18,570 --> 00:23:20,770
I guess my stomach will burst with just one of these.

330
00:23:20,770 --> 00:23:22,860
Thank you for the food.

331
00:23:25,690 --> 00:23:27,940
All of this, out of nowhere?

332
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:30,160
What do you mean out of nowhere?

333
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:32,390
I'm thanking you for that day.

334
00:23:32,390 --> 00:23:34,570
Why did you order so much when it's just two people?

335
00:23:34,570 --> 00:23:36,070
I can tell at a glance it's enough for three people.

336
00:23:36,070 --> 00:23:38,290
No, not at all.

337
00:23:38,290 --> 00:23:40,610
I just want you to eat up, Hyung.

338
00:23:41,510 --> 00:23:44,780
You're doing things on a bigger scale ever since you became president.

339
00:23:52,090 --> 00:23:54,230
What happened to that industrial spy?

340
00:23:54,230 --> 00:23:55,570
What?

341
00:23:56,930 --> 00:23:58,190
We're still looking.

342
00:23:58,190 --> 00:24:01,560
Gosh, it must be a headache.

343
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:03,740
That's not the only thing giving me a headache.

344
00:24:03,740 --> 00:24:07,450
Just because you're a president doesn't mean you live in peace.

345
00:24:07,450 --> 00:24:09,360
The higher-ups nag at you and

346
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:11,240
the employees fight with each other.

347
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:12,770
Hey...

348
00:24:14,780 --> 00:24:20,260
I mean, why would you bother making things hard and earning money by working?

349
00:24:20,260 --> 00:24:22,400
Don't you know Beomyeong Car is at an all-time high?

350
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:25,650
Just quit it all and go into stocks.

351
00:24:26,580 --> 00:24:27,940
Should I?

352
00:24:27,940 --> 00:24:30,230
Yes, quit it all!

353
00:24:30,230 --> 00:24:32,380
Okay. This hell of a job!

354
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:34,570
I'll quit right–

355
00:24:45,580 --> 00:24:47,340
Hyung...

356
00:24:47,340 --> 00:24:49,270
What's wrong?

357
00:24:53,340 --> 00:24:55,220
What's going on?

358
00:24:56,730 --> 00:24:58,160
What's this?
[Silver Lining, Deposit: 22,500,000 won]

359
00:24:58,160 --> 00:25:01,580
Where... Where did you get this money?

360
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:05,940
I guess it's my salary.

361
00:25:12,020 --> 00:25:13,510
Wow...

362
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:18,090
A president's pay is... definitely on a different level.

363
00:25:18,090 --> 00:25:20,010
Right?

364
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:25,920
Hey, our pay used to be a virtual currency.

365
00:25:26,780 --> 00:25:28,740
Are there places that pay with crypto?

366
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:30,250
That's not it.

367
00:25:30,250 --> 00:25:35,580
The numbers leave a mark in our bank accounts for a second and disappear.

368
00:25:35,580 --> 00:25:37,590
That's also true.

369
00:25:37,590 --> 00:25:40,660
I was so shocked because

370
00:25:40,660 --> 00:25:42,630
they disappeared so quickly.

371
00:25:42,630 --> 00:25:45,390
Gosh, I'm going insane. Why isn't it coming in?

372
00:25:45,390 --> 00:25:47,240
It's today, right?

373
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:50,510
We waited a month. What's one more day?

374
00:25:50,510 --> 00:25:53,800
Hey, it's because I'm excited.

375
00:25:57,920 --> 00:26:01,170
Hey, what are you going to do with your first pay?

376
00:26:01,170 --> 00:26:02,650
Me?

377
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:07,660
A premium beef set for my parents...

378
00:26:07,660 --> 00:26:09,950
- How is that?
- Wow. Hey, that sounds good!

379
00:26:09,950 --> 00:26:10,790
- Right?
- Yes!

380
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:13,200
Yes, we'll also do our duties as sons for once!

381
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,670
We're doing it!

382
00:26:17,890 --> 00:26:19,600
It's finally here.

383
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:21,960
Let me see.

384
00:26:23,870 --> 00:26:25,980
H-Hyung... We're rich.

385
00:26:25,980 --> 00:26:29,400
We're rich! We're rich!

386
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:32,770
Hello, we have first-grade Korean beef.

387
00:26:32,770 --> 00:26:34,350
Please give me the 130,000 won set.

388
00:26:34,350 --> 00:26:36,530
No, please give us the 150,000 won set.

389
00:26:36,530 --> 00:26:38,300
- Yes, please make it two.
- Okay.

390
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:39,970
Gosh...

391
00:26:43,290 --> 00:26:46,070
Thank you. Wow...

392
00:26:52,570 --> 00:26:58,800
[Payments Made, Remaining Balance: 50,000 won]

393
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:02,060
[Payments Made, Remaining Balance: 48,516 won]

394
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:12,950
Let's just...

395
00:27:12,950 --> 00:27:15,290
I'm sorry.

396
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:22,710
Let's go!

397
00:27:27,390 --> 00:27:29,410
Are you crying?

398
00:27:30,770 --> 00:27:33,300
No, I'm not.

399
00:27:33,300 --> 00:27:36,600
But you bought the tuna set, at least. I...

400
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:40,650
brought home a toothpaste set.

401
00:27:40,650 --> 00:27:42,220
But still...

402
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:46,540
they were happy their son bought it with his pay,

403
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:49,070
which made me feel worse.

404
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:53,390
I know...

405
00:27:54,150 --> 00:27:57,260
It's useless raising a child.

406
00:27:57,610 --> 00:27:59,140
This won't do.

407
00:27:59,140 --> 00:28:01,480
I'm going to the departmental store next time, no matter what.

408
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:02,940
Deal.

409
00:28:02,940 --> 00:28:05,890
Let's do our duties as sons after twenty-nine years!

410
00:28:05,890 --> 00:28:08,030
Let's do it!

411
00:28:08,860 --> 00:28:10,380
Oh, the bus is here.

412
00:28:10,380 --> 00:28:12,240
- Take care, Hyung.
- Bye.

413
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:18,150
[Account Transaction History]

414
00:28:20,540 --> 00:28:22,710
Excuse me...

415
00:28:22,710 --> 00:28:24,630
this month's caretaking fee...

416
00:28:24,630 --> 00:28:26,730
I sent the money. Please check.

417
00:28:26,730 --> 00:28:28,390
I did check.

418
00:28:28,390 --> 00:28:29,800
But...

419
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:33,050
I wanted you to give me a raise.

420
00:28:49,930 --> 00:28:52,480
It's a transfer.

421
00:28:54,150 --> 00:28:56,590
One moment, please! I'm getting off!

422
00:28:56,590 --> 00:28:58,090
Excuse me.

423
00:28:58,090 --> 00:29:00,160
Sorry. Thank you.

424
00:29:00,160 --> 00:29:01,630
I'm going home now.

425
00:29:01,630 --> 00:29:03,260
Okay.

426
00:29:06,820 --> 00:29:08,350
[Current Balance: 232,350 won]

427
00:29:24,610 --> 00:29:26,160
I'm sorry.

428
00:29:27,380 --> 00:29:30,800
I want to apologize for doing whatever I wanted to do.

429
00:29:49,930 --> 00:29:51,960
I regretted it a lot

430
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:54,130
after you left, Se Yeon.

431
00:29:54,130 --> 00:29:57,160
Because I know someone

432
00:29:57,720 --> 00:30:00,700
I never want to forgive or reconcile.

433
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:04,740
You do, In Seong?

434
00:30:04,740 --> 00:30:06,250
Yes.

435
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:09,850
I was too rude

436
00:30:09,850 --> 00:30:13,050
when I don't even have the right.

437
00:30:13,050 --> 00:30:15,350
Even your apology

438
00:30:15,350 --> 00:30:18,250
is so like you, In Seong.

439
00:30:25,250 --> 00:30:26,930
Your mother

440
00:30:26,930 --> 00:30:30,000
has such pretty hands.

441
00:30:33,970 --> 00:30:38,020
She worked so hard with her hands all her life without a single day of them being dry.

442
00:30:38,940 --> 00:30:42,760
She gets to keep them dry only after she collapses.

443
00:30:48,190 --> 00:30:51,270
I wanted to become a hotelier.

444
00:30:54,280 --> 00:30:55,340
[Dubai Imperial Hotel, Letter of Acceptance]

445
00:30:56,950 --> 00:30:57,910
Accepted!

446
00:30:57,910 --> 00:30:59,320
I got accepted!

447
00:30:59,320 --> 00:31:00,330
Accepted!

448
00:31:00,330 --> 00:31:03,830
I got accepted!

449
00:31:03,830 --> 00:31:06,220
I got accepted!
[Dear Mom]

450
00:31:07,010 --> 00:31:09,490
What do I do?

451
00:31:09,490 --> 00:31:11,710
Mom, I got accepted–

452
00:31:19,570 --> 00:31:22,470
[Surgery in Progress]

453
00:31:22,470 --> 00:31:24,250
She collapsed from partial paralysis

454
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:26,180
due to an acute stroke and,

455
00:31:26,180 --> 00:31:27,290
in the process,

456
00:31:27,290 --> 00:31:30,160
her head experienced a severe injury.

457
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,950
She's alive, but

458
00:31:35,950 --> 00:31:39,480
she basically has no consciousness.

459
00:31:41,610 --> 00:31:45,460
You'll have to prepare for a long fight.

460
00:31:51,770 --> 00:31:54,300
[Jobs]

461
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,660
[In the order of highest wage]

462
00:31:58,660 --> 00:32:01,970
[Salary: 40 million won - 70 million won]

463
00:32:01,970 --> 00:32:02,990
[Salary: 40 million won - 70 million won]

464
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:05,520
[IT Company, Silver Lining President's Secretary for Hire]

465
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,780
[IT Company, Silver Lining President's Secretary for Hire]

466
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:16,270
[IT Company, Silver Lining President's Secretary for Hire]

467
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:25,350
I wanted to let her enjoy luxurious vacations

468
00:32:25,350 --> 00:32:28,480
on a bed with great views.

469
00:32:29,840 --> 00:32:31,830
The reality is that...

470
00:32:32,810 --> 00:32:36,980
she can't get away from the hospital bed even for a day.

471
00:32:39,150 --> 00:32:41,070
Se Yeon...

472
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:45,170
I wanted to give you an answer.

473
00:32:46,830 --> 00:32:49,410
You had asked me

474
00:32:49,410 --> 00:32:52,600
about what my dream is at the campsite.

475
00:32:54,130 --> 00:32:57,310
Thanks to you, although short-lived,

476
00:32:58,110 --> 00:33:00,490
I was reminded of those days and...

477
00:33:01,610 --> 00:33:04,220
my heart raced a bit.

478
00:33:13,790 --> 00:33:15,940
The situation doesn't look good.

479
00:33:21,510 --> 00:33:24,090
As the launch date of the self-driving cars changed to October 3,

480
00:33:24,090 --> 00:33:27,200
Beomyeong Car's share price is increasing alarmingly.

481
00:33:29,290 --> 00:33:32,670
If the end-of-year shareholders' meeting is held like this,

482
00:33:32,670 --> 00:33:36,420
then my dear niece will end up sitting in the chairman's seat.

483
00:33:36,980 --> 00:33:38,830
What would you like to do?

484
00:33:40,930 --> 00:33:43,030
This won't do.

485
00:33:43,810 --> 00:33:47,780
I'll need to meet President Park In Seong in person.

486
00:34:02,500 --> 00:34:05,710
[Beomyeong Department Store]

487
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:07,670
Thank you.

488
00:34:10,510 --> 00:34:12,690
Aigoo, thank you.

489
00:34:12,690 --> 00:34:14,020
Hyung, I'll pay for these.

490
00:34:14,020 --> 00:34:15,790
Aigoo, no, thank you.

491
00:34:15,790 --> 00:34:17,750
Why would you pay for a gift for my parents?

492
00:34:17,750 --> 00:34:20,480
Come on, I do owe you a lot for everything.

493
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:21,930
I also got my first pay.

494
00:34:21,930 --> 00:34:25,730
Hey, my Beomyeong Car shares also went to the moon.

495
00:34:25,730 --> 00:34:27,510
Okay, then, but I'm buying the food.

496
00:34:27,510 --> 00:34:28,900
Okay.

497
00:34:29,460 --> 00:34:32,590
Hey, let's also buy them some clothes so they can stop wearing baggy pants.

498
00:34:32,590 --> 00:34:33,970
Sounds great!

499
00:34:33,970 --> 00:34:36,450
We lack swag but not money, right?

500
00:34:36,450 --> 00:34:38,050
We also have swag.

501
00:34:38,050 --> 00:34:39,430
Okay!

502
00:34:39,430 --> 00:34:41,650
Yes!

503
00:35:08,690 --> 00:35:11,540
Hello, how may I help you?

504
00:35:11,540 --> 00:35:14,130
From here to there.

505
00:35:14,130 --> 00:35:16,050
Please wrap them all up.

506
00:35:16,050 --> 00:35:18,020
Thank you!

507
00:35:23,100 --> 00:35:25,200
Baby, let's go!

508
00:35:29,600 --> 00:35:31,120
Love?

509
00:35:31,570 --> 00:35:33,700
Don't make me laugh. I'll buy it with money now.

510
00:35:33,700 --> 00:35:35,180
I'll just have to buy it with money.

511
00:35:35,180 --> 00:35:36,580
How much will it take?

512
00:35:36,580 --> 00:35:38,650
How much do you want?

513
00:35:43,410 --> 00:35:45,250
What's wrong with you?

514
00:35:46,170 --> 00:35:48,740
What were you thinking for your face to turn red?

515
00:35:48,740 --> 00:35:50,710
You're suspicious.

516
00:35:50,710 --> 00:35:53,300
It's nothing. L-Let's go.

517
00:35:59,860 --> 00:36:01,950
In Seong, In Seong!

518
00:36:01,950 --> 00:36:03,410
I feel like someone keeps following us.

519
00:36:03,410 --> 00:36:04,570
Whom?

520
00:36:04,570 --> 00:36:05,920
The suit toward the four o'clock direction.

521
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:08,220
Don't look back and act natural.

522
00:36:08,220 --> 00:36:10,380
Oh, he's my bodyguard.

523
00:36:10,380 --> 00:36:12,130
Oh, the bodyguard.

524
00:36:13,820 --> 00:36:15,460
Wow...

525
00:36:23,550 --> 00:36:25,410
This is a little small.

526
00:36:25,410 --> 00:36:28,010
I don't think you're supposed to wear it there...

527
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:56,310
I can't keep addressing you, "excuse me, hello, or hey."

528
00:36:57,030 --> 00:36:59,740
What should I call you?

529
00:37:00,340 --> 00:37:02,480
No need to exchange names.

530
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:04,530
They call him Mapi.

531
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:07,210
Mapi?

532
00:37:08,690 --> 00:37:10,880
Are you a mafia?

533
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:16,600
The legendary fists that even destroyed his opponents' mouthpieces.

534
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:18,490
That's why they call him Mapi.

535
00:37:18,490 --> 00:37:21,530
He was a promising boxer who was also a young national athlete,

536
00:37:21,530 --> 00:37:25,710
but now he's a loan shark with three criminal records, including assault and blackmailing.

537
00:37:28,430 --> 00:37:33,060
If you were going to throw it in my face anyway, why did you bother with a background check?

538
00:37:37,820 --> 00:37:41,810
I needed to fact-check it myself.

539
00:37:41,810 --> 00:37:46,800
If you run your trap without care, I'll have four criminal records.

540
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:49,300
That's what you call a fact.

541
00:37:52,540 --> 00:37:55,080
Wow, it's a balloon.

542
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:57,530
How do you do that?

543
00:38:00,330 --> 00:38:01,830
Gosh, so hideous.

544
00:38:01,830 --> 00:38:04,750
She'll get scared if you stare at her with a rugged face.

545
00:38:04,750 --> 00:38:06,610
You should smile for a child.

546
00:38:06,610 --> 00:38:09,370
Gosh, how can a person be like that?

547
00:38:18,830 --> 00:38:20,760
My, my. My goodness.

548
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:22,140
C-Come here.

549
00:38:22,140 --> 00:38:23,900
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm okay.

550
00:38:23,900 --> 00:38:25,260
- Oh, my.
- He's not scary at all.

551
00:38:25,260 --> 00:38:27,600
He's like Ha Seung from the Joy Classroom.

552
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:30,820
He teases me and takes my snacks every day,

553
00:38:30,820 --> 00:38:35,310
but the teacher said he's doing it because he likes me.

554
00:38:44,250 --> 00:38:45,250
Here.

555
00:38:45,250 --> 00:38:46,990
What's this for?

556
00:38:46,990 --> 00:38:49,900
It's just a shirt for you.

557
00:38:51,940 --> 00:38:54,490
Why would you give me this?

558
00:38:57,130 --> 00:38:59,910
In Seong, c-could it be that...

559
00:39:06,880 --> 00:39:09,560
you threw out the shirt I gave you?

560
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:12,240
You didn't need to buy a new one.

561
00:39:12,240 --> 00:39:14,290
I also threw out your shirt.

562
00:39:14,290 --> 00:39:16,640
I didn't think we'd meet again.

563
00:39:18,250 --> 00:39:20,460
- I see...
- Secretary Jeong.

564
00:39:20,460 --> 00:39:23,030
What time was the VR seminar again?

565
00:39:24,030 --> 00:39:26,060
It's two o'clock at Daejeon Expo Plaza.

566
00:39:26,060 --> 00:39:29,030
In Seong, please go there in my place.

567
00:39:29,030 --> 00:39:31,570
If it's in Daejeon, could I stop by my parents' house after?

568
00:39:31,570 --> 00:39:33,250
Sure. You can do that.

569
00:39:46,350 --> 00:39:49,800
You came all this way, so why don't you come inside with me?

570
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,800
No thanks.

571
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:59,550
When I was buying the gifts, Mapi...

572
00:40:00,710 --> 00:40:03,560
A-Anyway, I bought one for you, too.

573
00:40:05,500 --> 00:40:07,260
It's a wristwatch.

574
00:40:07,260 --> 00:40:12,520
I saw that you were using a watch for many purposes back then.

575
00:40:12,520 --> 00:40:15,610
I bought one with strong durability.

576
00:40:15,610 --> 00:40:17,740
I hope you like it.

577
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:01,040
My goodness!

578
00:41:01,040 --> 00:41:03,940
It's the purple dress I like.

579
00:41:03,940 --> 00:41:05,310
My goodness.

580
00:41:05,310 --> 00:41:07,850
You always wear the same clothes every day, Mom.

581
00:41:07,850 --> 00:41:09,920
Oh, my. You picked a good one.

582
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:13,390
Father, you like premium Korean beef.

583
00:41:15,250 --> 00:41:18,150
You just have plenty of money to throw away, right?

584
00:41:18,150 --> 00:41:21,770
This is how you become an idiot by wasting money like this left and right.

585
00:41:21,770 --> 00:41:23,820
He said he bought it since it was his first pay.

586
00:41:23,820 --> 00:41:24,660
What?

587
00:41:24,660 --> 00:41:29,480
You need to save every penny since you started out later than others.

588
00:41:29,480 --> 00:41:30,800
What?

589
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:34,100
Why do you keep comparing him with other people?

590
00:41:34,100 --> 00:41:38,030
Should I compare Jo Yong Pil and Lee Yong then?

591
00:41:38,740 --> 00:41:40,480
You just try!

592
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:42,250
I'm confident.

593
00:41:43,780 --> 00:41:46,030
- How could you...
- Father!

594
00:41:47,810 --> 00:41:49,880
- Here you go.
- What's that?

595
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:51,730
Glasses?

596
00:41:52,850 --> 00:41:57,760
Is it a declaration of war or something, telling me to open my eyes correctly?

597
00:41:57,760 --> 00:42:01,260
Come on, it's not like that. Geez...

598
00:42:01,260 --> 00:42:02,650
Try them on first.

599
00:42:02,650 --> 00:42:03,570
Forget it.

600
00:42:03,570 --> 00:42:05,030
Geez, don't be like that.

601
00:42:05,030 --> 00:42:06,520
- Why do I need glasses?
- Come on!

602
00:42:06,520 --> 00:42:07,760
- It'll look good on you.
- I don't need

603
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:09,570
- glasses.
- Come on.

604
00:42:18,130 --> 00:42:19,350
Honey?

605
00:42:19,350 --> 00:42:21,060
W-Wait, what are you–

606
00:42:21,060 --> 00:42:25,180
Baro, please play Jo Yong Pil's Mona Lisa.

607
00:42:53,960 --> 00:42:57,390
Oh, my! Darling!
♫ Even if I give you my all ♫

608
00:42:57,390 --> 00:43:02,070
- Over there...
- What?
♫ Can't I catch that heart? ♫

609
00:43:02,070 --> 00:43:03,280
Oh, my!

610
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:05,000
♫ You without a smile ♫

611
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:06,760
Honey! Honey!

612
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:08,720
♫ You are the Mona Lisa ♫

613
00:43:08,720 --> 00:43:10,030
Honey, what's wrong with you?

614
00:43:10,030 --> 00:43:11,580
Honey, Honey!

615
00:43:11,580 --> 00:43:14,610
♫ With a sad look ♫

616
00:43:14,610 --> 00:43:15,730
♫ Should I look and turn around? ♫

617
00:43:15,730 --> 00:43:17,680
Sir! I love you!
♫ Should I look and turn around? ♫

618
00:43:17,680 --> 00:43:19,750
Aigoo, Sir!

619
00:43:19,750 --> 00:43:23,140
Sir!

620
00:43:23,140 --> 00:43:24,930
- Get yourself together!
- Over there...

621
00:43:24,930 --> 00:43:26,880
Sir Jo Yong Pil is there.

622
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:29,870
Have you gone crazy? What's wrong with you?

623
00:43:29,870 --> 00:43:31,400
Pull yourself together!

624
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:33,960
- Aigoo, did he get possessed?
- Hey!

625
00:43:35,500 --> 00:43:38,540
- What?
- Try closing your eyes!

626
00:43:38,540 --> 00:43:40,480
♫ I linger by your side ♫

627
00:43:40,480 --> 00:43:42,250
- Don't be shocked.
- Okay, okay.

628
00:43:42,250 --> 00:43:44,860
Now, open your eyes!

629
00:43:45,510 --> 00:43:48,140
- Wait, it's him...
- Aigoo...

630
00:43:48,140 --> 00:43:49,590
It's Jo Yong Pil, isn't it?

631
00:43:49,590 --> 00:43:52,850
- How is it?
- Your dad will stand tall with the foreman now.

632
00:43:52,850 --> 00:43:56,060
I knew he would like it more than the beef.

633
00:43:57,060 --> 00:44:02,140
By the way, how could a pair of glasses show Jo Yong Pil whenever you put them on?

634
00:44:02,660 --> 00:44:04,650
They're called AR glasses.

635
00:44:04,650 --> 00:44:07,100
Our company made them.

636
00:44:07,120 --> 00:44:09,890
A-AR?

637
00:44:10,620 --> 00:44:12,600
Yes.

638
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:16,770
Mom, do you remember doing a video call with me?

639
00:44:16,770 --> 00:44:19,150
Wow... Oh, my!

640
00:44:19,150 --> 00:44:20,780
Wh-What's this here?

641
00:44:20,780 --> 00:44:26,290
Back then, I put a flower on my face and even a dog face too, right?

642
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:30,710
I laughed out loud back then.

643
00:44:30,710 --> 00:44:32,600
Those glasses are the same.

644
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:34,940
Inside the real world that Dad is seeing,

645
00:44:34,940 --> 00:44:38,300
there's a Jo Yong Pil in there, created with graphics.

646
00:44:38,300 --> 00:44:39,890
I see...

647
00:44:39,890 --> 00:44:42,160
So you're saying...

648
00:44:42,160 --> 00:44:45,590
that Jo Yong Pil is fake, right?

649
00:44:45,590 --> 00:44:48,290
Wow, it's as good as the real one.

650
00:44:48,290 --> 00:44:49,640
Sir...

651
00:44:49,640 --> 00:44:52,480
- Aigoo, Sir!
- I'll go take this call, Mom.

652
00:44:52,480 --> 00:44:54,590
Aigoo, Sir!

653
00:44:54,590 --> 00:44:57,010
Aigoo!

654
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:02,530
I'm sorry. I took too long, right?

655
00:45:02,530 --> 00:45:07,160
How did you think of giving your parents AR glasses as a gift?

656
00:45:07,160 --> 00:45:08,230
Sorry?

657
00:45:08,230 --> 00:45:10,090
You did really well.

658
00:45:10,090 --> 00:45:12,820
Is this worth a compliment?

659
00:45:12,820 --> 00:45:15,300
Of course, you should be complimented.

660
00:45:15,300 --> 00:45:21,420
Thanks to you, I thought of an ISE that can put Director Kwak in his place.

661
00:45:26,630 --> 00:45:29,550
[President Park In Seong]

662
00:45:34,070 --> 00:45:35,450
Will this work?

663
00:45:35,450 --> 00:45:37,720
Technology-wise, it's perfect.

664
00:45:37,720 --> 00:45:40,710
There should be no problem if the teamwork is good.

665
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:46,320
[Kim Seon Ju]

666
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:50,110
You need to aim for when Director Kwak falls asleep.

667
00:45:50,110 --> 00:45:52,110
Thank you.

668
00:45:52,110 --> 00:45:54,290
- Director!
- What?

669
00:45:54,290 --> 00:45:55,540
Aigoo.

670
00:45:55,540 --> 00:45:57,850
I enjoyed the meal, thanks to you, President Park.

671
00:45:57,850 --> 00:46:01,630
I'm sorry for cornering you that day without evidence.

672
00:46:01,630 --> 00:46:03,030
Here you go again.

673
00:46:03,030 --> 00:46:04,910
If the misunderstanding has been cleared, that's it.

674
00:46:04,910 --> 00:46:07,240
Now, I'm full and getting sleepy.

675
00:46:07,240 --> 00:46:08,290
Why don't we go for some coffee?

676
00:46:08,290 --> 00:46:09,720
I'll pay for the coffee.

677
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:12,780
No, I'll buy the coffee as well.

678
00:46:16,130 --> 00:46:18,300
Well, well...

679
00:46:21,120 --> 00:46:22,230
Is it this place?

680
00:46:22,230 --> 00:46:23,580
Yes. The view

681
00:46:23,580 --> 00:46:26,170
from the sky lounge is great.

682
00:46:26,170 --> 00:46:29,380
How is every elevator broken?

683
00:46:29,380 --> 00:46:30,830
Where is the worker here?

684
00:46:30,830 --> 00:46:32,060
Let's use the stairs...

685
00:46:32,060 --> 00:46:33,890
since we need to digest.

686
00:46:33,890 --> 00:46:35,610
To the sky lounge?

687
00:46:35,610 --> 00:46:38,110
Yes. Let's go.

688
00:46:50,230 --> 00:46:52,150
With all this work,

689
00:46:56,340 --> 00:46:58,690
I think the coffee will be delicious.

690
00:46:58,690 --> 00:47:00,200
Right?

691
00:47:02,700 --> 00:47:04,630
President Park...

692
00:47:08,470 --> 00:47:10,540
by now...

693
00:47:10,540 --> 00:47:12,460
don't you think they would've fixed it all?

694
00:47:12,460 --> 00:47:13,710
Come on.

695
00:47:13,710 --> 00:47:15,080
We're almost there.

696
00:47:15,080 --> 00:47:17,760
Just think of it as an exercise and walk up.

697
00:47:22,100 --> 00:47:23,650
[21st Floor]

698
00:47:24,300 --> 00:47:26,640
Fifteen more floors?

699
00:47:26,640 --> 00:47:28,590
We'll be there in no time.

700
00:47:28,590 --> 00:47:30,890
Let's go, let's go.

701
00:47:30,890 --> 00:47:33,880
Aigoo, I'm dying...

702
00:47:40,970 --> 00:47:42,340
The 36th floor?

703
00:47:42,340 --> 00:47:44,100
The 36th floor...

704
00:48:06,730 --> 00:48:08,590
It's locked.

705
00:48:08,590 --> 00:48:09,850
Really?

706
00:48:09,850 --> 00:48:12,440
Let's have coffee next time then.

707
00:48:14,200 --> 00:48:15,520
What?

708
00:48:16,230 --> 00:48:17,450
What are you doing?

709
00:48:17,450 --> 00:48:19,080
Lunchtime is almost over.

710
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:20,900
We need to go back to work.

711
00:48:22,190 --> 00:48:24,000
Descending now.

712
00:48:56,170 --> 00:48:58,570
You should put on your seatbelt.

713
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:05,860
Here.

714
00:49:09,050 --> 00:49:12,350
Secretary Jeong, Director Kwak looks tired.

715
00:49:12,350 --> 00:49:15,100
Please turn on the massage feature.

716
00:49:36,340 --> 00:49:38,470
He's sleeping. He's sleeping now.

717
00:49:49,790 --> 00:49:51,590
Secretary Jeong...

718
00:49:52,810 --> 00:49:55,100
some music.

719
00:49:55,100 --> 00:49:56,910
Turn on some music.

720
00:49:59,760 --> 00:50:01,940
Okay, I understand.

721
00:50:14,660 --> 00:50:17,560
Gosh, this song is so nice.

722
00:50:19,110 --> 00:50:21,420
Isn't that so, Director Kwak?

723
00:51:08,250 --> 00:51:11,130
Gosh, Secretary Jeong,

724
00:51:11,880 --> 00:51:14,930
you should've woken me up if we were here.

725
00:51:22,020 --> 00:51:24,270
Secretary Jeong...

726
00:51:27,380 --> 00:51:29,270
President Kim!

727
00:51:35,160 --> 00:51:38,900
There's no way President Kim could be here.

728
00:51:38,900 --> 00:51:42,310
Why did you do that at the golf course that day?

729
00:51:42,310 --> 00:51:44,710
Why did you do that to me?

730
00:51:45,820 --> 00:51:47,530
I also...

731
00:51:48,290 --> 00:51:50,900
I also did it because I was instructed to.

732
00:52:37,180 --> 00:52:39,600
Did you have a nice dream?

733
00:52:41,010 --> 00:52:42,960
That's not it...

734
00:52:43,820 --> 00:52:45,630
It's too late for you to try to get out of it.

735
00:52:45,630 --> 00:52:49,380
There's no way President Kim could be here.

736
00:52:50,080 --> 00:52:51,890
I also...

737
00:52:52,490 --> 00:52:55,100
I also did it because I was instructed to.

738
00:52:56,220 --> 00:52:59,910
I know that you're not the one who planned everything.

739
00:52:59,910 --> 00:53:04,310
You don't have what it takes as far as your personality or guts.

740
00:53:04,310 --> 00:53:06,610
Who made you do it?

741
00:53:06,610 --> 00:53:08,210
Pardon?

742
00:53:08,870 --> 00:53:10,240
Well...

743
00:53:10,240 --> 00:53:12,660
I don't know what you're talking about...

744
00:53:12,660 --> 00:53:19,470
I don't know how deeply you are involved in this,

745
00:53:19,470 --> 00:53:21,960
but you know this...

746
00:53:22,980 --> 00:53:27,070
President Kim Seon Ju was attacked.

747
00:53:29,130 --> 00:53:31,310
Attacked, you say?

748
00:53:31,310 --> 00:53:36,580
Isn't he taking a sabbatical due to his health condition?

749
00:53:37,370 --> 00:53:39,850
You can continue to pretend not to know.

750
00:53:39,850 --> 00:53:41,320
It's just that...

751
00:53:41,320 --> 00:53:46,530
I'm curious about what will happen when they cut out off the tail.

752
00:53:47,700 --> 00:53:49,320
Right...

753
00:53:50,570 --> 00:53:56,540
Do you think they'll protect you to the end or...

754
00:53:57,240 --> 00:54:01,160
will they pretend not to know anything, just as you're doing?

755
00:54:20,740 --> 00:54:23,560
How did you take care of things?

756
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:27,310
The kid seems to know about everything.

757
00:54:30,010 --> 00:54:31,640
No.

758
00:54:31,640 --> 00:54:33,510
I can't trust you guys.

759
00:54:33,510 --> 00:54:36,540
I'm going to visit him in person and tell him.

760
00:54:46,230 --> 00:54:49,440
Do you think Director Kwak will move as we had planned?

761
00:54:50,030 --> 00:54:53,830
His safety is of foremost importance to him.

762
00:54:53,830 --> 00:54:59,220
If he's cornered, he'll line up with someone else for his survival.

763
00:54:59,220 --> 00:55:04,090
Human nature cannot tolerate it when things are unfair.

764
00:55:04,090 --> 00:55:08,640
If he doesn't want to take the blame, I'm sure he'll fess up to us.

765
00:55:10,500 --> 00:55:14,200
I'm sure he'll contact you.

766
00:55:23,000 --> 00:55:24,400
[Vice Chairman Oh Yeong Geun]

767
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:26,400
Human nature...

768
00:55:28,050 --> 00:55:29,530
Hello?

769
00:55:32,160 --> 00:55:33,950
Yes, Vice Chairman.

770
00:55:40,900 --> 00:55:44,000
The apple was so tasty.

771
00:55:44,000 --> 00:55:48,400
You can be proud of your parents' work.

772
00:55:48,400 --> 00:55:50,600
I heard that it's very challenging

773
00:55:50,600 --> 00:55:53,900
to grow apple trees. Is that true?

774
00:55:55,100 --> 00:55:57,400
It's a difficult tree species.

775
00:55:57,400 --> 00:55:59,300
It must be.

776
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:02,300
The sweeter the fruit,

777
00:56:02,300 --> 00:56:05,600
the more pests it will attract.

778
00:56:07,040 --> 00:56:09,520
Why did you ask me to come?

779
00:56:20,100 --> 00:56:25,400
Just like how your parents grow apple trees,

780
00:56:25,400 --> 00:56:30,800
I gave my whole life to growing Beomyeong.

781
00:56:30,800 --> 00:56:32,800
But...

782
00:56:32,800 --> 00:56:36,600
at some point, a pest kept

783
00:56:36,600 --> 00:56:39,400
digging holes in my tree.

784
00:56:40,300 --> 00:56:42,600
What do you do at times like this?

785
00:56:42,600 --> 00:56:44,000
If the situation is too grave,

786
00:56:44,000 --> 00:56:47,700
we cut it out or burn it to avoid even bigger losses.

787
00:56:49,600 --> 00:56:52,200
I like that!

788
00:56:52,200 --> 00:56:55,300
It's the same with business management.

789
00:56:57,500 --> 00:57:01,000
My rash niece said

790
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:05,200
she'd launch self-driving cars.

791
00:57:08,400 --> 00:57:10,400
You know this already.

792
00:57:10,400 --> 00:57:12,900
She's just playing her cards with the press.

793
00:57:14,400 --> 00:57:17,100
Why do you think that?

794
00:57:18,400 --> 00:57:20,000
That's because...

795
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:24,800
President Kim Seon Ju is in a situation where he can't pull that off.

796
00:57:27,000 --> 00:57:29,000
Isn't that right?

797
00:57:32,800 --> 00:57:34,900
Hey, you were asleep.

798
00:57:34,900 --> 00:57:36,200
I'm sorry.

799
00:57:36,200 --> 00:57:37,800
How is Min Ju?

800
00:57:39,400 --> 00:57:40,900
No, no.

801
00:57:40,900 --> 00:57:43,200
I was just wondering if everything's okay.

802
00:57:46,400 --> 00:57:48,400
Yes, I just called.

803
00:57:48,400 --> 00:57:50,100
Go back to sleep.

804
00:57:50,100 --> 00:57:51,600
I'm hanging up.

805
00:58:51,040 --> 00:58:55,240
[Room 316]

806
00:59:04,080 --> 00:59:06,950
Do you know the symbolic meaning of apples?

807
00:59:08,350 --> 00:59:10,820
Temptation, wisdom,

808
00:59:10,820 --> 00:59:13,120
and success.

809
00:59:15,200 --> 00:59:18,600
Go home and think wisely about

810
00:59:18,600 --> 00:59:21,200
whom you're going to stand next to.

811
00:59:23,300 --> 00:59:25,900
I will not stand next to anyone.

812
00:59:28,800 --> 00:59:31,200
Youth sure is a good thing.

813
00:59:31,200 --> 00:59:33,100
But you know...

814
00:59:34,000 --> 00:59:36,800
unless you stand next to me,

815
00:59:36,800 --> 00:59:41,100
I can't guarantee your safety, either.

816
00:59:42,940 --> 00:59:46,070
Are you threatening me right now?

817
00:59:47,100 --> 00:59:50,100
Oh, no. No way...

818
00:59:51,600 --> 00:59:53,000
Just...

819
00:59:53,000 --> 00:59:57,300
think of it as a concern coming from an old geezer.

820
01:00:36,300 --> 01:00:39,480
[Impyeong Mental Hospital]

821
01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:24,400
Did Vice Chairman say such a thing?

822
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:31,600
Yes.

823
01:01:31,600 --> 01:01:34,600
Whether he's saying that because he knows something,

824
01:01:34,600 --> 01:01:37,600
or he's trying to find out something...

825
01:01:38,750 --> 01:01:40,970
I just can't figure it out.

826
01:01:52,400 --> 01:01:54,200
Hello?

827
01:01:54,200 --> 01:01:56,100
This is Kwak Sam Su.

828
01:02:03,200 --> 01:02:05,200
Yes, Director Kwak.

829
01:02:05,200 --> 01:02:07,100
Let's meet.

830
01:02:07,100 --> 01:02:09,000
I have something to give you.

831
01:02:11,500 --> 01:02:14,000
- To me?
 - I'll tell you the truth

832
01:02:14,000 --> 01:02:16,000
about that day.

833
01:02:16,000 --> 01:02:18,000
Please come out alone.

834
01:02:56,300 --> 01:02:58,200
Director Kwak, wake up.

835
01:02:58,200 --> 01:03:00,000
Director Kwak!

836
01:03:05,600 --> 01:03:07,600
Unless you stand next to me,

837
01:03:07,600 --> 01:03:11,500
I can't guarantee your safety, either.

838
01:03:14,200 --> 01:03:15,600
Director Kwak!

839
01:03:15,600 --> 01:03:18,600
Director Kwak! Wake up!

840
01:03:24,800 --> 01:03:26,400
H-Help me!

841
01:03:26,400 --> 01:03:28,900
Hurry and call an ambulance!

842
01:03:29,800 --> 01:03:32,100
Wake up! Director Kwak!

843
01:03:45,800 --> 01:03:48,800
No. He called me and asked me to meet him.

844
01:03:48,800 --> 01:03:50,500
He wouldn't kill himself like this.

845
01:03:50,500 --> 01:03:52,400
Yes, yes...

846
01:03:52,400 --> 01:03:55,000
I think so, too. Get him.

847
01:03:56,000 --> 01:03:59,800
All right, everything you say from this point on

848
01:03:59,800 --> 01:04:03,000
could be used against you in court.

849
01:04:03,000 --> 01:04:05,200
So if you're scared,

850
01:04:07,200 --> 01:04:10,000
it's better to stay silent.

851
01:04:13,400 --> 01:04:14,900
What...

852
01:04:52,010 --> 01:04:56,350
♫ When I'm worried, I can trust in myself ♫

853
01:04:56,350 --> 01:05:00,160
♫ I'll just try to get my life back ♫

854
01:05:00,200 --> 01:05:06,200
♫ Everything can freeze from my heart soon ♫

855
01:05:06,200 --> 01:05:08,600
♫ Over you ♫

856
01:05:08,600 --> 01:05:13,200
♫ Send me free right now ♫

857
01:05:15,000 --> 01:05:18,900
[Unlock My Boss]

858
01:05:18,900 --> 01:05:20,500
What should I do?

859
01:05:21,380 --> 01:05:24,380
Is there any other way? We toss him out.

860
01:05:25,600 --> 01:05:27,400
Did you hear from In Seong?

861
01:05:27,400 --> 01:05:28,200
No, I haven't heard.

862
01:05:28,200 --> 01:05:30,000
More complex the situation is, make it simple.

863
01:05:30,000 --> 01:05:31,600
I looked up the number that called me

864
01:05:31,600 --> 01:05:35,400
and looks like it's near the Yeongpo Airport.

865
01:05:35,400 --> 01:05:36,600
What are you doing right now?

866
01:05:36,600 --> 01:05:37,900
Things will worsen if they know you're with me.

867
01:05:37,900 --> 01:05:39,800
If he had left the base,

868
01:05:39,800 --> 01:05:42,000
he should've just run without looking back.

869
01:05:42,000 --> 01:05:45,100
If he was going to hesitate, he should've stayed in the base.

870
01:05:45,100 --> 01:05:49,400
Okay, bring me the next base in here.
